{
  "stem": "4693.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This guy-- doctor, he was a doctor and baptized, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Didn't help him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I and the doctor-- Ole was his name-- I and him were later, by night, thrown over the border.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we went a little bit and came back again to go to the next.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I can tell you, it was a very difficult thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because it was very cold, it was freezing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had a piece of bread, I had to throw it out because it was completely frozen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We couldn't use it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We got out in the next town, and we, again, were taken to the military commander.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Unfortunately, as we were escorted to him, a guy from the army group-- which was in the previous town-- saw us and he denounced us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the camp, on the 31st of December-- this was 24th of December, we were arrested-- on the 31st of December, we were loaded into trucks from Germany to Russia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After a few days, I think six or seven days-- very cold conditions, freezing conditions, goods trucks-- we arrived at the station.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I saw the writing on the station-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's a Swedish burial place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I knew that the Sweden were-- attacked Russia, and the the Russian-- hit very strongly near Poltava, and over on the Swedes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I knew that we were somewhat close to Poltava.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I knew Poltava-- this is where we're taken to jail.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was in Poltava jail for a few months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was in a small cell with three others, with whom I didn't have any communication.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I was, more, or less, all the day talking to myself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] The Poltava jail was comparatively clean, we are four, only.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
